PrecisAmendment to Order in Council P.C. 1998-232 which authorized the issuance of a Proclamation in connection with the minting of a SET OF SILVER COINS replicating the 50¢, 25¢, ten, five and one-cent coins first produced in 1908, in order to correct an error in the references to the metallic composition of the one-cent coin.
